# Mentor (Socrates)

`MentorBubble.tsx` is the AI chat component. Completions depend on **`NessoSettings.aiMode`**:

- **`local`** (default) ‚Äî In-browser **WebGPU** inference via `@mlc-ai/web-llm` in `src/llm/webllm.ts`. `App.tsx` runs `localModelWeightsCached()` and, when true, `initWebLLM()` when `aiMode === 'local'` so the MLC engine starts loading without opening Settings first. First-time download still uses **Download & use** in Settings when nothing is cached. `MentorBubble` subscribes with `useWebLLM()` (status, `progress`, `progressText`) for a loading bar, placeholder, and transcript message; chat input stays disabled until `status === 'ready'`. `getEngine()` exposes `MLCEngine` for `engine.chat.completions.create` with the same message shape as the remote path.

- **`remote`** ‚Äî OpenAI-compatible **`POST ‚Ä¶/chat/completions`** via `fetch`. Base URL, model, and optional API key come from `aiBaseUrl`, `aiModel`, `aiApiKey`; there is no environment-variable fallback for the key.

## Setup

Configure under **Settings** (gear, **‚åò,**): **Appearance**, **AI**, **Review** (FSRS live in **Review** for the full-screen review overlay only), **Data** (erase locally persisted graphs/settings).

## Persona

Socrates is a Socratic mentor: mostly questions, almost no lecturing. Rules live in **`getMentorBase()`** inside `MentorBubble.tsx`:

- No graph edits in dialogue (do not propose new nodes/edges or renames).
- Default one short question; explain only to frame it; aim under ~180 words (hard cap via `MENTOR_MAX_TOKENS`).
- No emojis or flattery; sparse `*asterisks*` on key terms; no JSON or pseudo-graph markup.
- No em dash (U+2014) in replies; use commas, periods, or short sentences instead.
- English **legend** decodes FSRS-shaped node tokens in the snapshot (`(new)`, `s=‚Ä¶d`, days since review, Again/Hard/Good/Easy, `DUE`); reply language stays separate (`Respond in Italian.` when UI is Italian).

## System prompt (single chat)

There are **no mode tabs**. `buildGraphChatPrompt()` builds one system string: graph snapshot ‚Äî up to `MAX_SNAPSHOT_NODES` nodes tagged with stability, days since last review, FSRS rating, optional DUE (`nodeDesc`), sorted weakest-first via **`nodeStrength()`** (`src/llm/context.ts`; stability‚Äëfirst with Again/Hard and light overdue tweaks), remainder summarized if larger), up to `MAX_SNAPSHOT_EDGES` edges (`2√ó` the node cap by default), optional selection (node or full edge path), optional **`Focus:` / `Related:`** lines from **`buildFocalNeighborContext()`** in `src/llm/context.ts` when a node is selected ‚Äî plus **`getMentorBase()`**. Each send recomputes the prompt from the live store so new edits appear on the next turn.

On panel open, graph switch, local-model-ready transition, or **`chatKey`** bump (header refresh), the first mentor line is fetched using a short synthetic **user** turn from **`buildMentorSeedText()`**: wording depends on whether a **node**, an **edge only**, or **nothing** is selected.

## Rendering

Assistant replies render as plain text with subtle emphasis via **`Typewriter`** (`emphasis` prop). User-authored bubbles remain plain text in a `<span>`.

## Selection vs history

`history` remains local component state. The opening synthetic user message reflects **`selectedNode` / `selectedEdge`** via **`buildMentorSeedText()`**; subsequent turns still rebuild `buildGraphChatPrompt()` from the live selection on each send.

## Panel open/closed

Whether the mentor **card** is expanded is `mentorPanelExpanded` on `useGraphStore`, updated via `setMentorPanelExpanded`. It is persisted with the rest of UI chrome (`zustand` `persist` ‚Üí localStorage). The FAB remains visible when collapsed.

## Message history

`history: Message[]` is local to `MentorBubble` (not in the store). It resets when the panel opens again, the graph changes, local engine readiness changes during the opening sequence, or the user clicks **New chat** (refresh). Do not persist chat history to the store.

## API call

**Remote:** `fetch(`${aiBaseUrl}/chat/completions`, ‚Ä¶)` with JSON body:

- `model` ‚Äî `settings.aiModel`
- `max_tokens` ‚Äî `MENTOR_MAX_TOKENS` (~380, aligned with ~180-word replies)
- `messages` ‚Äî `[{ role: 'system', content: buildGraphChatPrompt() }, ‚Ä¶]` plus full `history` turns mapped to `user` / `assistant` roles.

`Authorization: Bearer ‚Ä¶` is sent when `settings.aiApiKey` is non-empty.

**Local:** After `initWebLLM()` completes, `getEngine()` from `webllm.ts` is non-null. Until then the UI blocks sends. Then `engine.chat.completions.create({ model: LOCAL_MODEL_ID, max_tokens: MENTOR_MAX_TOKENS, messages })` with the same `messages` array built for remote mode.
